A funny thing happened on its way to becoming a science: economics seldom tested its premises empirically.
That’s something that “physics envy” can’t capture—that the social nature of human beings makes any laws of behavior tentative and contextual.
In fact, the very term “social science” is probably best seen as an oxymoron.
